</div>
<button class="accordion">What should the duty of candour annual report include?
</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>The duty of candour annual report must include accurate information about the number and nature of incidents to which the duty of candour procedure has been applied concerning a health service, a care service or a social work service.
</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What does lack of candour mean?
</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>“Candour” is the quality of being open and honest. It has a similar meaning to frankness. Hence, someone displaying a lack of candour is not being frank with you. Although they may not be lying, they are not telling the whole truth.
</p>
</div>
<button class="accordion">Does the duty of candour apply to staff?
</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>All healthcare organisations have a duty to support their staff to report adverse incidents and to encourage them to be open and honest with patients if something goes wrong with their care.
</p>
